  "texts": [
    "Recall also that we view L as an End(adM)-valued one-form on B.",
    "The following is a generalisation of [Lot07, Proposition 4.17].Lemma 2.18.",
    "The decomposition of ∇ ad into a connection preserving h and a h-self-adjoint End(adM)valued one-form is(18) ∇ ad = ∇ LC -L,where ∇ LC is induced by the Levi-Civita connection on M. Consequently, the tension field of h is given by(19) τ (h)(U, U) = 2 n i=1 (∇ g Xi L) Xi Û, Û.If ∇ ad is flat, then τ (h) is the tension field (in the sense of harmonic maps) of the ρ-equivariant map h: ( B, gB) → (Sym 2 + (𝔫 *), g sym).Proof.",
    "Recall [NT18, Lem.",
    "8.1] that ∇ ad is determined by the relation∇ ad X U ∧ = [ X, Û].Using that ∇ g is torsion free, and that the bracket of vertical and basic vector fields is is vertical, we have[ X, Û] = V∇ g X Û -V∇ g Û X.By definition, the section of adM corresponding to the first term on the right-hand-side is ∇ LC X U."
